{:synth/id   :chaos-henon
 :synth/tags [:chaos :henon :discrete-map :arc-ready]
 :synth/doc  "Hénon map chaotic oscillator audio voice.

  The Hénon map is a 2D discrete dynamical system: xₙ₊₁ = 1 - a·xₙ² + yₙ.
  At audio rate (freq=22050 Hz) it produces a distinctive thin, metallic chaos
  with a crisper texture than Lorenz — the Hénon attractor is a fractal set of
  parallel curves rather than a smooth butterfly.

  The :chaos parameter [0..1] controls the a parameter:
    chaos=0.0  → a=1.0   — period-2 cycle, clean tone (two pitches alternating)
    chaos=0.3  → a=1.2   — period-4, rich harmonics beginning
    chaos=0.45 → a=1.25  — chaos onset, sharp timbral transition
    chaos=0.7  → a=1.4   — classic Hénon attractor, metallic fizz
    chaos=1.0  → a=1.6   — deep chaos, dense metallic noise

  The period-doubling route to chaos (1→2→4→8→chaos) is audible as pitch
  subdivision: a clean tone splits into two frequencies, then four, then an
  inharmonic swarm. This is distinctly different from Lorenz's smooth drift.

  The Hénon output has a narrower dynamic range than Lorenz (approximately ±1.5)
  so no normalization divisor is needed.

  A gentle RLPF shapes the metallic spectrum. The default :freq-cut 3200 Hz keeps
  the crispness while taming harshness.

  Primary use: metallic percussion textures, chaotic hi-hat-like rhythms (low chaos),
  electronic noise bursts (high chaos). The period-doubling transition at chaos 0.4–0.5
  is compositionally the most interesting region.

  Apply-trajectory! usage:
    (apply-trajectory! node :chaos
      (trajectory :from 0.0 :to 0.7 :beats 16 :curve :lin :start (now)))
  sweeps from tonal through period-doubling into chaotic metallic texture."
 :args  {:freq-cut  3200.0
         :freq-res  0.5
         :chaos     0.5
         :b         0.3
         :amp       0.5
         :attack    0.02
         :release   1.5
         :pan       0.0}
 :graph [:out 0
          [:pan2
           [:* [:env-gen [:asr :attack 1.0 :release] :gate :amp]
               [:rlpf
                [:mix [[:henon 22050 [:+ 1.0 [:* 0.6 :chaos]] :b 0.0 0.0]]]
                :freq-cut
                :freq-res]]
           :pan]]}
